      { id: 'B', text: 'B. Replace the monitoring job with a custom SQL script designed to calculate statistics on the features and predictions within BigQuery.' },
      { id: 'C', text: 'C. Decrease the sample_rate parameter in the RandomSampleConfig of the monitoring job.' },
      { id: 'D', text: 'D. Increase the monitor_interval parameter in the ScheduleConfig of the monitoring job. Explanation: Overall explanation Incorrect Answers: A. Replace the monitoring job with a DataFlow pipeline that utilizes TensorFlow Data Validation (TFDV). While TFDV is a powerful tool for generating descriptive statistics of your data, detecting anomalies, and understanding your dataset, setting up a DataFlow pipeline to replace Vertex AI Model Monitoring involves developing and maintaining additional infrastructure. This could potentially introduce more complexity and might not necessarily lead to cost savings. B. Replace the monitoring job with a custom SQL script designed to calculate statistics on the features and predictions within BigQuery. Writing custom SQL scripts to calculate statistics on the features and predictions could provide insights into data drift, but it requires manual effort to develop, execute, and maintain these scripts. This approach also lacks the automated, continuous monitoring and alerting capabilities provided by Vertex AI Model Monitoring. D. Increase the monitor_interval parameter in the ScheduleConfig of the monitoring job. Increasing the interval at which the monitoring job runs would reduce the frequency of drift checks, potentially lowering costs. However, extending the monitoring interval could delay the detection of data drift, which might compromise the model\'s performance and the promptness of drift detection. Correct Answer C. Decrease the sample_rate parameter in the RandomSampleConfig of the monitoring job. Reducing the sample_rate parameter would mean that a smaller fraction of the incoming requests (and corresponding predictions) are logged and analyzed for drift detection. This approach directly addresses the goal of reducing the cost associated with model monitoring because it decreases the volume of data being processed and stored for monitoring purposes. By carefully selecting a new, lower sample rate, you can balance the need for cost reduction with the requirement to adequately sample the traffic for meaningful drift detection. This strategy allows for continued monitoring of the model\'s performance with less resource utilization. Reference: https://cloud.google.com/vertex-ai/docs/modelmonitoring/overview#considerations' }
