      { id: 'C', text: 'C. Configure VPC Peering with Vertex AI, and specify the network of the training job.' },
      { id: 'D', text: 'D. Download the data to a Cloud Storage bucket before calling the training job. Explanation: Overall explanation Incorrect Answers: B. Create a Cloud Run endpoint as a proxy to the data. Use Identity and Access Management (IAM) authentication to secure access to the endpoint from the training job. This method does not inherently minimize the risk of data exfiltration as effectively as VPC Service Controls. While IAM provides authentication, it doesn\'t offer the same level of network-based isolation and control over data movement. C. Configure VPC Peering with Vertex AI, and specify the network of the training job. Is a good practice for establishing network connectivity. Still, without the additional protective boundary that VPC Service Controls offer, it might not fully address the stringent data governance and security requirements. D. Download the data to a Cloud Storage bucket before calling the training job. Could expose sensitive data to potential risks if not properly secured or if the bucket permissions are not correctly managed. This method also involves moving data outside of its original secure environment, which could increase the risk of exfiltration. Correct Answer A. Enable VPC Service Controls for peerings, and add Vertex AI to a service perimeter. VPC Service Controls provide an additional layer of security that helps to mitigate the risk of data exfiltration by creating a secure boundary around your Google Cloud resources. By defining a service perimeter, you can control the flow of data across the boundary of your Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) network, ensuring that sensitive data does not leave the secured environment. Adding Vertex AI to a service perimeter allows your machine learning and data processing activities within Vertex AI to access the internal data securely while being protected by VPC Service Controls. This setup ensures that the training jobs can access the necessary data through API endpoints hosted within your project\'s network without exposing the data to external threats. Reference: https://cloud.google.com/security/vpc-service-controls' }
